to connect virtual machine postgresql  to pgAdmin 
to understand server -> client (server is virtual machine postgresql and client is pgAdmin)

step 1:- to check postgresql is running or not if not start the service
systemctl start postgresql17.service | postgresql
step 2:- check the IP ADDRESS :- hostname -I | ip a | ifconfig
step 3:- verify the configration file listen_addresses if the liste_address is localhost then change to * 
path /var/lib/pgsql/16/data/postgresql.conf =>  listen_addresse="*"
step 4:- add the enrty in hostbased authentication for configure client Authentication 
path /var/lib/pgsql/16/data/pg_hba.conf => add the fields
| replication | user | ip address | method 
host | all | all | 0.0.0.0/0 | scram-sha-256
all changes after restart the service

step 5:- Allow firewall port :- for postgresql uses port 5432
firewall-cmd --add-port=5432/tcp --permanent
after add must reload :- firewall-cmd --reload
too check :- firewall-cmd --list-ports
